news.title: U.S. payrolls rose by 130,000 in January, more than expected; unemployment rate at 4.3%
news.summary: Job growth was stronger than expected to start 2026, providing some relief to concerns about the state of the U.S. labor market.

news.title: FAA abruptly lifts order halting El Paso airport flights for 10 days
news.summary: The FAA has halted flights at El Paso International Airport for 10 days. The FAA has suspended all flights at the airport for the duration of the shutdown.

news.title: Kraft Heinz pauses work to split the company as new CEO says 'challenges are fixable'
news.summary: Kraft Heinz CEO Steve Cahillane said many of the company's issues are "fixable" Kraft Heinz is the world's largest producer of ketchup.

news.title: Scripps launches cost cutting, AI integration in latest effort to generate earnings growth
news.summary: CEO Adam Symson said the changes are intended to alleviate journalists from administrative tasks, but not replace them with AI. Symson: The changes are not intended to replace journalists with artificial intelligence.

news.title: Apptronik raises $520 million to beat Chinese humanoids, Tesla Optimus to market
news.summary: Apollo humanoids are being tested in factories and warehouses with partners Mercedes-Benz and GXO Logistics. Apptronik's Apollo humanoids will be available in the U.S. in 2015.

news.title: Morgan Stanley just pored through 3,600 stocks and says these are the best opportunities from the AI shakeout
news.summary: Morgan Stanley strategists offer criteria on how to find the AI winners. They say the market is starting to demand proof of return on equity.

news.title: T-Mobile sees huge boom in phone subscribers, but here’s why the stock is falling
news.summary: Investors were looking for more from the wireless carrier when it came to subscriber growth and profit. The wireless carrier is expected to make a profit for the first time in three years.

news.title: My husband, 73, wants to sell our $300K rental and buy an annuity. Is that wise?
news.summary: He believes the annuity will net $1,600 per month, the same as the rent from the house. “He believes he will be able to retire at the age of 70,” his son says.

news.title: Kraft Heinz puts separation plans on hold so it can focus on fixing these problems
news.summary: Kraft Heinz's stock falls as sales again disappointed, particularly in North America. Kraft Heinz’s stock falls to a two-year low.
